{"id":14881771,"mediaExerciseId":"deb7a91b-d710-4e79-97bb-9918f07f2026","exerciseName":"3","chapterName":"21","chapterTitle":"International Corporate Finance","groupId":612471,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":736,"solutions":[{"id":5982489,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are asked to determine the following amounts using the concept of forward exchange rates.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**Exchange rate** is the value of a country's currency when express in *another country's currency*.  A **forward trade** is an agreement to *exchange currency in the future*. The *exchange rate in the agreement* of a forward trade is called a **forward exchange rate**.\n\nWe will look at Figure 21.1 of this book to answer the questions in the exercise.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/ed3a3f0341771dc341573b2d06a6309d/91032a66b94408e7adb16a0a97983161/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/ed3a3f0341771dc341573b2d06a6309d/91032a66b94408e7adb16a0a97983161/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"## a.\n\nWe are asked  to identify the the six-month forward rate for the Japanese yen in yen per U.S. dollar and determine if the yen is selling at a premium or a discount.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":213,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/ed3a3f0341771dc341573b2d06a6309d/ab2986d4097a9f360e68aa65cdccb1d5/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":108,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/ed3a3f0341771dc341573b2d06a6309d/ab2986d4097a9f360e68aa65cdccb1d5/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"We can see in Figure 21.1 that the **six-month forward rate** for a Japanese yen per dollar is **¥ 102.21 = $1**.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"For us to determine if the yen is selling at a premium or a discount, we need to compare the forward rate to the **spot rate**. The spot rate is the exchange rate in a spot trade. The **spot trade** is an agreement to exchange currencies based on the exchange rate on that date and must be settled within two business days.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"The six-month forward rate of a Japanese Yen in dollars is $ 0.009784. On the other hand, the spot rate of a Japanese yen in dollar is $ 0.009773. We can see that the value of the Japanese Yen expressed in dollars is *greater when the six-month forward rate is used*. Hence, the **yen is selling at a premium**.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":179,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/ed3a3f0341771dc341573b2d06a6309d/6fcb21d45e8ee8cfdc717ae9090c404b/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":91,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/ed3a3f0341771dc341573b2d06a6309d/6fcb21d45e8ee8cfdc717ae9090c404b/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"As a conclusion, the **six-month forward rate** is **¥ 102.21 = $1** and the yen is selling at a **premium**.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/ed3a3f0341771dc341573b2d06a6309d/bb241d270e4d7862f20039fd743a703c/lateximg_large.png","width":1623},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/ed3a3f0341771dc341573b2d06a6309d/bb241d270e4d7862f20039fd743a703c/lateximg.png","width":812}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7},{"columns":[{"text":"## b.\n\nWe are asked  to identify the three-month forward rate for Australian dollars in U.S. dollars per  Australian dollar and determine if dollar selling at a premium or a discount.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":8},{"columns":[{"text":"We can see in Figure 21.1 that the **three-month forward rate** for Australian dollars in U.S. dollars per  Australian dollar  is **$ 0.9216 = A$1**.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":9},{"columns":[{"text":"For us to determine if the yen is selling at a premium or a discount, we need to compare the forward rate to the **spot rate**. The spot rate is the exchange rate in a spot trade. The **spot trade** is an agreement to exchange currencies based on the exchange rate on that date and must be settled within two business days.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/ed3a3f0341771dc341573b2d06a6309d/f517e3c65f82e3291cdb74cb8ac60ac3/lateximg_large.png","width":1022},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/ed3a3f0341771dc341573b2d06a6309d/f517e3c65f82e3291cdb74cb8ac60ac3/lateximg.png","width":511}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":10},{"columns":[{"text":"The three-month forward rate of an Australian dollar in dollars is $ 0.9216. On the other hand, the spot rate of a Australian dollar in dollar is $ 0.9274. We can see that the value of the Australian dollar expressed in dollars is *greater when the spot rate is used*. Hence, the **Australian dollar is selling at a discount**.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":179,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/ed3a3f0341771dc341573b2d06a6309d/26d367104ddb0532bbaf59165adb94c3/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":91,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/ed3a3f0341771dc341573b2d06a6309d/26d367104ddb0532bbaf59165adb94c3/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":11},{"columns":[{"text":"As a conclusion, the **three-month forward rate** is **$ 0.9216 = A$1** and the Australian dollar is selling at a **discount**.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":136,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/ed3a3f0341771dc341573b2d06a6309d/40c6247e4e0d5fcb082d88255b8f1b55/lateximg_large.png","width":1741},"regular":{"height":69,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/ed3a3f0341771dc341573b2d06a6309d/40c6247e4e0d5fcb082d88255b8f1b55/lateximg.png","width":871}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":12},{"columns":[{"text":"## c.\n\nWe are asked to determine what will happen to the value of the dollar relative to the yen and the Australian dollar, based on the information in the figure 21.1.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/ed3a3f0341771dc341573b2d06a6309d/28d3359dd5d7ae4bbcbcb524b6bfd942/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/ed3a3f0341771dc341573b2d06a6309d/28d3359dd5d7ae4bbcbcb524b6bfd942/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":13},{"columns":[{"text":"We have already determine the values of the Australian dollar and Japanese yen when express in U.S dollars on a spot rate and forward exchange rate.  Since the yen is selling at a **premium** in the future, more U.S. dollar is required to purchase a yen. Therefore, the **U.S. dollar will decrease relative to the yen**.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":14},{"columns":[{"text":"On the other hand, the Australian dollar is selling at a **discount** in the future. As a result, less U.S. dollar is required to purchase an Australian dollar. Therefore, the **U.S dollar will increase relative to the Australian dollar**.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":179,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/ed3a3f0341771dc341573b2d06a6309d/689407c2c7bfd7d3c91ee72176de4a0e/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":91,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/ed3a3f0341771dc341573b2d06a6309d/689407c2c7bfd7d3c91ee72176de4a0e/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":15},{"columns":[{"text":"As a conclusion, U.S. dollar will **decrease relative to the yen** and **will increase relative to the Australian dollar**.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":138,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/ed3a3f0341771dc341573b2d06a6309d/bdd977fbe04c73f24ceb59ac2071f56c/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":70,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/ed3a3f0341771dc341573b2d06a6309d/bdd977fbe04c73f24ceb59ac2071f56c/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":16},{"columns":[{"text":"To sum it all up, we have determined the following amounts using the concept of forward exchange rates.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":63,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/ed3a3f0341771dc341573b2d06a6309d/554beba3cf169bce3f15c3913fa8f93f/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":32,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/ed3a3f0341771dc341573b2d06a6309d/554beba3cf169bce3f15c3913fa8f93f/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":17}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"5aaf1c0a-e673-4c17-aa28-c9f439479adf","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":17}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881772,"exerciseName":"4","page":736,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"b166febb-2cbe-433c-8f6a-970c5eb732a6","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-21-questions-and-problems-4-b166febb-2cbe-433c-8f6a-970c5eb732a6"},{"id":14881773,"exerciseName":"5","page":737,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"df9f73a2-77ea-468f-87b0-7ad10d18c572","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-21-questions-and-problems-5-df9f73a2-77ea-468f-87b0-7ad10d18c572"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881770,"exerciseName":"2","page":736,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"128c11ec-0c32-4a2c-9e12-e45ab05a0878","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-21-questions-and-problems-2-128c11ec-0c32-4a2c-9e12-e45ab05a0878"},{"id":1488176